The weather is set to get chilly and wet in Gauteng as cold air blasts into the province from the Western coast. Sunday is likely to be balmy with temperatures set to plummet from Monday. On Friday the prediction is that on Sunday in Gauteng the temperature will go up to around 21°C. On Monday there's a 90% chance of rain across the day with the top temperature falling to 13°C. On Tuesday the expected low is 5°C. "Snowfalls can also be expected on the high mountains over the north east of the Eastern Cape bordering Lesotho from Saturday," Weather SA said. The weather is expected to become slightly warmer from Thursday. Here's your five-day weather forecast for Johannesburg, Pretoria, Durban, Cape Town and Port Elizabeth: